# Built-in AF_VSOCK guest support so `ssh root@vsock%$(vm cid stub)` works from
# the host. QEMU is launched with -device vhost-vsock-pci, so this is the guest
# side: the AF_VSOCK core plus the virtio (guest) transport.
#
# NOTE ON =y vs the stock default: gentoo-kernel's base config is the per-arch
# Fedora config (sys-kernel/gentoo-kernel copies kernel-<arch>-fedora.config into
# .config; gentoo-kernel-config only layers fragments on top). That Fedora config
# ALREADY enables these as MODULES (=m) on every arch, so you do NOT need to list
# them here just to get them compiled -- gentoo-kernel-bin ships them as modules
# for exactly this reason. We force =y instead to pull activation as early as
# possible: built-in means the transport is live from boot with no dependency on
# module autoload timing, which matters for ssh-over-vsock that we rely on early.
#
# (If =m were acceptable, simply NOT disabling it would suffice. The earlier
# `# CONFIG_VSOCKETS is not set` in unset.config was overriding the Fedora =m and
# killing vsock outright; that line has been removed and we pin =y here instead.)
CONFIG_VSOCKETS=y
CONFIG_VIRTIO_VSOCKETS=y
